        "# Modeling and Evaluation\n",
        "\n",
        "From this point on, we keep the feature set fixed and change one imbalance-handling choice at a time. That makes it easier to see whether performance changes come from the metric, the weighting scheme, or the resampling method rather than from the rest of the pipeline.\n",
        "\n",
        "For the first three strategies below, we follow the same routine: fit on the training set, calibrate the selected model's decision threshold on the full tuning split with AutoGluon's native F1 objective, evaluate on the untouched test set, and then inspect held-out calibration plots as a descriptive diagnostic.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Data\n",
        "\n",
        "-   The target label is `TX_FRAUD`, which indicates whether a transaction is fraudulent (1) or not (0).\n",
        "\n",
        "-   The list of final features exclude features that are not relevant for modeling, such as IDs and datetime columns."
