      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Ignore Class Imbalance Approach\n",
        "\n",
        "**Rationale:**\n",
        "\n",
        "-   The observed class imbalance is part of the business problem, not automatically a defect in the data.\n",
        "-   Before changing the data, it is worth asking how far a strong learner can get with the original base rate.\n",
        "-   Many modern machine learning estimators can still rank rare fraud cases reasonably well if the features are informative and the evaluation setup is sensible, including:\n",
        "    -   Tree-based ensembles (LightGBM, XGBoost, CatBoost)\n",
        "    -   Neural networks\n",
        "-   This baseline matters because it tells us whether later imbalance-handling tricks are actually helping or just making the workflow more complicated.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Process:**\n",
        "\n",
        "1.  Train multiple estimators on the original, imbalanced dataset.\n",
