      "source": [
        "### SMOTE (Synthetic Minority Over-sampling Technique)\n",
        "\n",
        "SMOTE creates synthetic minority samples by interpolating between nearby minority instances. That can expand local fraud coverage without exact duplication, but if the minority class is too small the synthetic neighborhoods can become unstable."
      ],
      "id": "75bca02d"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: resampling-smote-prep\n",
        "\n",
        "minority_class_count_smote = y_train.value_counts().min()\n",
        "k_neighbors_smote = min(5, max(1, minority_class_count_smote - 1))\n",
        "if minority_class_count_smote <= 1:\n",
        "    print(\"Minority class count is too low for SMOTE. Using original data as fallback.\")\n",
        "    X_train_smote, y_train_smote = X_train.copy(), y_train.copy()\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    smote = SMOTE(random_state=2025, k_neighbors=k_neighbors_smote)\n",
        "    X_train_smote, y_train_smote = smote.fit_resample(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"SMOTE training data shape: {X_train_smote.shape}\")\n",
        "print(f\"SMOTE target distribution:\\n{y_train_smote.value_counts(normalize=True)}\")"
      ],
      "id": "resampling-smote-prep",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
